# PITCH NOTES

## **_LOGLINE_**

Set in modern Palm Springs, semi-retired photojournalist Mitch Sawyer and his husband Billy Charles become embroiled in a mystery when billionaire Clive WYNANT‚Äôs assistant is murdered and the whole Wynant family is suspect.

## **_GENRES_**

Mystery, LGBT, PALM SPRINGS, Noir, Comedy

## **_THE BIG QUESTION_**

Why do human beings believe people we know to be lying to us? 

Bill Clinton told us he didn‚Äôt have sex with ‚Äúthat woman‚Äù. OJ told us he didn‚Äôt kill his wife. Trump told us the virus would just ‚Äúgo away‚Äù and that he won an election he didn‚Äôt win. 

W.C. Fields is credited with saying ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs a sucker born every minute.‚Äù It‚Äôs hard to argue with that given that every day people are conned out of their money by charisma and persuasion and we buy it: Hook line and sinker. 

## **_SHORT PITCH_**

I‚Äôve tried to write this series multiple times with fits and starts. But when I stumbled onto this Mitch and Billy storyline, I knew I had what had previously alluded me: A really fun murder mystery in the spirit of movies like ‚ÄúThe Thin Man‚Äù and TV series like ‚ÄúHeart to Heart‚Äù and ‚ÄúMoonlighting‚Äù.

## **_SETTING_**

Enter the world of modern Palm Springs. The hippy-culture of the 60‚Äôs and California weed legalization of the 90‚Äôs has given way to a city that is not ashamed of enjoying the use of recreational drugs or trying polyamorous sex. In this world, everything about modern American monoculture is boring and bland next to the multicolor, poly-gendered and un-gendered ‚ÄúQUEER‚Äù culture. 

The story is an meditation on why humans trust people, despite reasonable doubt of their trustworthiness. Why do we believe ‚ÄúThe lies of handsome men‚Äù?

Come visit the world of Mr & Mr Charles.

